hh3cLI.name: hh3cLI
hh3cLI.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Tech. Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085

hh3cLIActive.name: hh3cLIActive
hh3cLIActive.description: This Notification is sent when a type of intercepting configuration is changed from inactive to active. The value of the hh3cLIStreamtype which identify the actual intercept stream is included in this notification.

hh3cLITimeOut.name: hh3cLITimeOut
hh3cLITimeOut.description: When the time specified in hh3cLIMediationTimeout arrives, the device notifies the manager corresponding intercept is removed.

hh3cLIFailureInformation.name: hh3cLIFailureInformation
hh3cLIFailureInformation.description: When interception is configured on distributed device, the configuration perhaps failed on some board. If this happened, this notification will occur.

hh3cLINewIndex.name: hh3cLINewIndex
hh3cLINewIndex.description: This object will be used as an index value for a new hh3cLIMediationEntry. Whenever read, the agent will give a non-used value. This is to reduce the probability of conflict during creation of new hh3cLIMediationTable entries.

hh3cLIMediationTable.name: hh3cLIMediationTable
hh3cLIMediationTable.description: This table describes interception gateway information with which interception device communicates.

hh3cLIMediationEntry.name: hh3cLIMediationEntry
hh3cLIMediationEntry.description: An entry of configuring mediation device.

hh3cLIMediationIndex.name: hh3cLIMediationIndex
hh3cLIMediationIndex.description: hh3cLIMediationIndex is a entry identifier. The Mediation Device should be responsible for making sure these are unique. Before creating a new entry, a value for this variable may be obtained by reading hh3cLINewIndex to reduce the probability of a value collision.

hh3cLIMediationDestAddr.name: hh3cLIMediationDestAddr
hh3cLIMediationDestAddr.description: The IP Address of the Mediation Device to receive intercepted traffic.

hh3cLIMediationDestPort.name: hh3cLIMediationDestPort
hh3cLIMediationDestPort.description: The L4-port number on the Mediation Device to receive intercepted traffic.

hh3cLIMediationSrcInterface.name: hh3cLIMediationSrcInterface
hh3cLIMediationSrcInterface.description: The interface on the intercepting device from which to transmit intercepted data. If zero, intercepting device will select an outbound interface according to hh3cLIMediationDestAddr.

hh3cLIMediationDscp.name: hh3cLIMediationDscp
hh3cLIMediationDscp.description: The Differentiated Services Code Point the intercepting device applies to the IP packets encapsulating the intercepted traffic.

hh3cLIMediationTimeOut.name: hh3cLIMediationTimeOut
hh3cLIMediationTimeOut.description: The time at which this row and all related Stream Table rows should be automatically removed, and the intercept function expire.

hh3cLIMediationTransport.name: hh3cLIMediationTransport
hh3cLIMediationTransport.description: The protocol used in transferring intercepted data to the Mediation Device.

hh3cLIMediationNotificationEnable.name: hh3cLIMediationNotificationEnable
hh3cLIMediationNotificationEnable.description: This variable controls the generation of any notifications or informs by the MIB agent for this table entry.

hh3cLIMediationRowStatus.name: hh3cLIMediationRowStatus
hh3cLIMediationRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry.

hh3cLIStreamTable.name: hh3cLIStreamTable
hh3cLIStreamTable.description: This table lists the traffic stream's type to be intercepted. The specified filter is defined in hh3cLIIPStreamTable, hh3cLIMACStreamTable or hh3cLIUserStreamTable, according to hh3cLIStreamtype. Also it contains counters for packets to be intercepted and dropped by attached type of filter.

hh3cLIStreamEntry.name: hh3cLIStreamEntry
hh3cLIStreamEntry.description: A single type of data stream to be intercepted.

hh3cLIStreamIndex.name: hh3cLIStreamIndex
hh3cLIStreamIndex.description: The index of the stream entry.

hh3cLIStreamtype.name: hh3cLIStreamtype
hh3cLIStreamtype.description: Identifies the type of stream, and according to it uses filter table. It can not be changed after a filter table is attached to it. The following types of streams are supported: ip: IP filter. The exact definition is a row in hh3cLIIPStreamTable. mac: MAC filter. The exact definition is a row in hh3cLIMACStreamTable. userConnecton: User connection filter. The exact definition is a row in hh3cLIUserStreamTable.

hh3cLIStreamEnable.name: hh3cLIStreamEnable
hh3cLIStreamEnable.description: If 'true', the interception is active. And it is set to 'true' only after an additional filter specification has been attached to this stream.

hh3cLIStreamPackets.name: hh3cLIStreamPackets
hh3cLIStreamPackets.description: The numbers of packets that have been intercepted.

hh3cLIStreamDrops.name: hh3cLIStreamDrops
hh3cLIStreamDrops.description: The numbers of packets were dropped in the lawful intercept process.

hh3cLIStreamHPackets.name: hh3cLIStreamHPackets
hh3cLIStreamHPackets.description: The numbers of packets have been intercepted. This object is a 64-bit version of hh3cLIStreamPackets.

hh3cLIStreamHDrops.name: hh3cLIStreamHDrops
hh3cLIStreamHDrops.description: The numbers of packets were dropped in the lawful intercept process. This object is a 64-bit version of hh3cLIStreamDrops.

hh3cLIStreamRowStatus.name: hh3cLIStreamRowStatus
hh3cLIStreamRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry.

hh3cLIIPStreamTable.name: hh3cLIIPStreamTable
hh3cLIIPStreamTable.description: This table lists the IPv4 and IPv6 streams to be intercepted. It is associated with hh3cLIMediationTable and hh3cLIStreamTable.

hh3cLIIPStreamEntry.name: hh3cLIIPStreamEntry
hh3cLIIPStreamEntry.description: A single stream to be intercepted. The first index indicates the Mediation Device. The second index is that of the stream's counter entry in the hh3cLIStreamTable. The second index permits multiple classifiers to be used together, such as having an IP address as source or destination.

hh3cLIIPStreamInterface.name: hh3cLIIPStreamInterface
hh3cLIIPStreamInterface.description: Traffic received or transmitted over this interface will be intercepted. This value must be set when creating a stream entry, either zero, or a valid interface index. If the value is zero, interception accepts any interface. Then at least one additional parameter must be selected, and not be default value.

hh3cLIIPStreamAddrType.name: hh3cLIIPStreamAddrType
hh3cLIIPStreamAddrType.description: The type of address, used in packet selection.

hh3cLIIPStreamDestAddr.name: hh3cLIIPStreamDestAddr
hh3cLIIPStreamDestAddr.description: The Destination address used in packet selection. This address will be consistent with the type specified in hh3cLIIPStreamAddrType.

hh3cLIIPStreamDestAddrLength.name: hh3cLIIPStreamDestAddrLength
hh3cLIIPStreamDestAddrLength.description: The length of the Destination Prefix. A value of zero means all addresses to match. This prefix length will be consistent with the type specified in hh3cLIIPStreamAddrType.

hh3cLIIPStreamSrcAddr.name: hh3cLIIPStreamSrcAddr
hh3cLIIPStreamSrcAddr.description: The Source Address used in packet selection. This address will be consistent with the type specified in hh3cLIIPStreamAddrType.

hh3cLIIPStreamSrcAddrLength.name: hh3cLIIPStreamSrcAddrLength
hh3cLIIPStreamSrcAddrLength.description: The length of the Source Prefix. A value of zero means all addresses to match. This prefix length will be consistent with the type specified in hh3cLIIPStreamAddrType.

hh3cLIIPStreamTosByte.name: hh3cLIIPStreamTosByte
hh3cLIIPStreamTosByte.description: The value of the TOS byte. If hh3cLIIPStreamTosByte&(~hh3cLIIPStreamTosByteMask)!=0, configuration is rejected.

hh3cLIIPStreamTosByteMask.name: hh3cLIIPStreamTosByteMask
hh3cLIIPStreamTosByteMask.description: This value is ANDed with the value of the TOS byte in a packet and compared with hh3cLIIPStreamTosByte. If the values are equal, the comparison is equal. If both the mask and the TosByte value are zero, the result is to always accept.

hh3cLIIPStreamFlowId.name: hh3cLIIPStreamFlowId
hh3cLIIPStreamFlowId.description: The flow identifier in an IPv6 header. -1 indicates that the Flow Id is unused.

hh3cLIIPStreamProtocol.name: hh3cLIIPStreamProtocol
hh3cLIIPStreamProtocol.description: The IP protocol to match against the IPv4 protocol number or the IPv6 Next- Header number in the packet.

hh3cLIIPStreamDestL4PortMin.name: hh3cLIIPStreamDestL4PortMin
hh3cLIIPStreamDestL4PortMin.description: The minimum value that the layer-4 destination port number in the packet must have in order to match. This value must be equal to or less than the value specified for this entry in hh3cLIIPStreamDestL4PortMax. If both hh3cLIIPStreamDestL4PortMin and hh3cLIIPStreamDestL4PortMax are at their default values, the port number is effectively unused. If hh3cLIIPStreamDestL4PortMin is equal to hh3cLIIPStreamDestL4PortMax, only one port number to be intercepted.

hh3cLIIPStreamDestL4PortMax.name: hh3cLIIPStreamDestL4PortMax
hh3cLIIPStreamDestL4PortMax.description: The maximum value that the layer-4 destination port number in the packet must have in order to match this classifier entry. This value must be equal to or greater than the value specified for this entry in hh3cLIIPStreamDestL4PortMin. If both hh3cLIIPStreamDestL4PortMin and hh3cLIIPStreamDestL4PortMax are at their default values, the port number is effectively unused. If hh3cLIIPStreamDestL4PortMin is equal to hh3cLIIPStreamDestL4PortMax, only one port number to be intercepted.

hh3cLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMin.name: hh3cLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMin
hh3cLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMin.description: The minimum value that the layer-4 destination port number in the packet must have in order to match. This value must be equal to or less than the value specified for this entry in hh3cLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMax. If both hh3cLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMin and hh3cLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMax are at their default values, the port number is effectively unused. If hh3cLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMin is equal to hh3cLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMax, only one port number to be intercepted.

hh3cLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMax.name: hh3cLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMax
hh3cLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMax.description: The maximum value that the layer-4 destination port number in the packet must have in order to match this classifier entry. This value must be equal to or greater than the value specified for this entry in hh3cLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMin. If both hh3cLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMin and hh3cLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMax are at their default values, the port number is effectively unused. If hh3cLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMin is equal to hh3cLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMax, only one port number to be intercepted.

hh3cLIIPStreamVRF.name: hh3cLIIPStreamVRF
hh3cLIIPStreamVRF.description: It is the name of a Virtual Routing and Forwarding (VRF) of a VPN.

hh3cLIIPStreamRowStatus.name: hh3cLIIPStreamRowStatus
hh3cLIIPStreamRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry.

hh3cLIMACStreamTable.name: hh3cLIMACStreamTable
hh3cLIMACStreamTable.description: This table lists the IEEE 802 streams to be intercepted. It is associated with hh3cLIMediationTable and hh3cLIStreamTable.

hh3cLIMACStreamEntry.name: hh3cLIMACStreamEntry
hh3cLIMACStreamEntry.description: A single stream to be intercepted. The first index indicates the Mediation Device. The second index is that of the stream's counter entry in the hh3cLIStreamTable. The second index permits multiple classifiers to be used together, such as having an MAC address as source or destination.

hh3cLIMACStreamFields.name: hh3cLIMACStreamFields
hh3cLIMACStreamFields.description: This object displays what attributes will be compared to identify traffic. interface: indicates that traffic on the stated interface is to be intercepted dstMacAddress: indicates that traffic destined to a given address should be intercepted srcMacAddress: indicates that traffic sourced from a given address should be intercepted ethernetPid: indicates that traffic with a stated Ethernet Protocol Identifier should be intercepted dSap: indicates that traffic with an certain 802.2 LLC Destination SAP should be intercepted sSap: indicates that traffic with an certain 802.2 LLC Source SAP should be intercepted At least one of the bits has to be set in order to activate an entry. If multiple bits are set, traffic to be intercepted must be satisfied with all set attributes.

hh3cLIMACStreamInterface.name: hh3cLIMACStreamInterface
hh3cLIMACStreamInterface.description: Traffic received or transmitted over this interface will be intercepted. This value must be set when creating a stream entry, either zero, or a valid interface index. If the value is zero, interception accepts any interface. Additional parameter must be selected together.

hh3cLIMACStreamDestAddr.name: hh3cLIMACStreamDestAddr
hh3cLIMACStreamDestAddr.description: The Destination address used in packet selection.

hh3cLIMACStreamSrcAddr.name: hh3cLIMACStreamSrcAddr
hh3cLIMACStreamSrcAddr.description: The Source Address used in packet selection.

hh3cLIMACStreamEthPid.name: hh3cLIMACStreamEthPid
hh3cLIMACStreamEthPid.description: The value of the Ethernet Protocol Identifier in the Ethernet traffic or IEEE 802.2 SNAP traffic.

hh3cLIMACStreamDSap.name: hh3cLIMACStreamDSap
hh3cLIMACStreamDSap.description: The value of the IEEE 802.2 Destination SAP.

hh3cLIMACStreamSSap.name: hh3cLIMACStreamSSap
hh3cLIMACStreamSSap.description: The value of the IEEE 802.2 Source SAP.

hh3cLIMACStreamRowStatus.name: hh3cLIMACStreamRowStatus
hh3cLIMACStreamRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry.

hh3cLIUserStreamTable.name: hh3cLIUserStreamTable
hh3cLIUserStreamTable.description: This table lists the user connection streams to be intercepted. It is associated with hh3cLIMediationTable and hh3cLIStreamTable.

hh3cLIUserStreamEntry.name: hh3cLIUserStreamEntry
hh3cLIUserStreamEntry.description: A single stream to be intercepted. The first index indicates the Mediation Device. The second index is that of the stream's counter entry in the hh3cLIStreamTable. This permits multiple classifiers to be used together.

hh3cLIUserStreamAcctSessID.name: hh3cLIUserStreamAcctSessID
hh3cLIUserStreamAcctSessID.description: This is the RADIUS attribute 44 acct-session-ID. The string must be set, and the length not be zero.

hh3cLIUserStreamRowStatus.name: hh3cLIUserStreamRowStatus
hh3cLIUserStreamRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry.
